notes: Fuck, chipped Evans9, whcih otherwise looked fantastic, with the metal tweasers while trying to remove it from the carbon tape Choongman used in the petri dish. Carbon tape doesn't come off, rips off, then I remove it from the bottom of the sample (upside down on mounting block) with ethanol and kimwipe. 01... Wow, it's tricky to get a steady O2 signal. This definitely does not do it (though, coincidentially, it gives me an approximately constant m/z=48 signal). Maybe constant potential would be better. At least everything is behaving as makes sense for a high-surface-area catalyst with lots of carbon junk on it and 100 Ohm behind the WE. Capacitance at 1 mV/s about 3/4 that of Evans6. Looks a bit less active than Evans6! Seeing clear OER at 80 mV overpotential, 7500s, but not really at 60 mV or 70 mV (8600 s). Cycled 10 times, pausing at endpoints (0 and +1.4 v vs RHE) 02... Damn, looks like crazy ohmic drop. Whatever, cycling at 20 mV/s, pausing at endpoints. This is the last in this round of 18O. Left with heating power source at 100 and a big drop of normal water on top.
